reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Goes down great!
reviews.reviewText: The biggest thing for me with any type of pills is if they work and if I can get them down!Pros:The work well enough to keep my iron levels up before and after donating blood, as I am a regular blood donor!They help keep the female iron levels steady and healthy throughout the normal monthly iron shifts that females deal with monthly (trying to put that politely). It's so important for women to maintain healthy iron levels during these times!They are super easy to swallow, they aren't too big, and they have no taste.They do not cause constipation or changes in bowel habits.I can get them on my subscribe-and-save, so I don't have to worry about remembering to re-order.Cons:Some people prefer to buy in bulk, like bottles in a 60 or 90 count. These only come in a 30-day supply, so you have to purchase monthly unless you add to subscribe-and-save (which is what I do).Pro-tip:Take iron with vitamin C (pill or a glass of orange juice) to increase absorption.
